.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2023" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell - basic UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter developed for the Holberton School project. It handles basic command-line operations, including simple commands with arguments, error handling, PATH resolution, and built-in commands.

.SH PROJECT INFORMATION
.B Project Team: Wilfried Leroulier, Julie Dedieu
.B Project Due Date: December 24, 2023

.SH LEARNING OBJECTIVES

Understand the basics of approaching a project
Implement a simple UNIX command interpreter
Comprehend the background context of shell development
.SH REQUIREMENTS

Editors: vi, vim, emacs
Compilation: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, gcc with options -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89
Code Style: Betty style
Memory Leaks: Not allowed
Functions per file: No more than 5
Header Files: Include guarded
System Calls: Use only when necessary
.SH TESTING

Interactive Mode:
.EX
$ ./simple_shell
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($)
($) exit
$
.EE
Non-Interactive Mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./simple_shell
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
$
$ cat test_ls_2 | ./simple_shell
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.EE
